## (5)(a) Three Use Cases of 5G

> Which are the three use cases of 5G? Explain each use case in detail using diagrams where possible. *(8 marks)*

> *Learn more: [5G Requirements](/wireless-communications/5g/requirements)*

---

**1. eMBB (Enhanced Mobile Broadband)**

High-speed data for bandwidth-hungry applications.

- **Peak speed:** 20 Gbps
- **Use cases:** 4K/8K video streaming, VR/AR, cloud gaming
- **Key feature:** Massive capacity in crowded areas (stadiums, concerts)

---

**2. URLLC (Ultra-Reliable Low-Latency Communication)**

Mission-critical applications where delay = danger.

- **Latency:** under 1 ms
- **Reliability:** 99.999%
- **Use cases:** Remote surgery, autonomous vehicles, industrial robots
- **Key feature:** Guaranteed delivery, no room for error

---

**3. mMTC (Massive Machine-Type Communication)**

Connecting billions of IoT devices.

- **Density:** 1 million devices per kmÂ²
- **Use cases:** Smart cities, agriculture sensors, asset tracking
- **Key feature:** Low power, long battery life (10+ years), small data packets

---

| Use Case | Speed | Latency | Devices | Example |
|----------|-------|---------|---------|---------|
| **eMBB** | 20 Gbps | ~10 ms | Few | VR streaming |
| **URLLC** | Medium | 1 ms | Few | Remote surgery |
